items.name: SOAP photo enhancer for SDXL [Shot On A Phone]
items.description:
I love SDXL. But the "photos" it creates are soooo.... DRAMATIC! Always with dark tones, soft lighting, and shallow depth of field. Do you ever just want photos that look like you took them on a phone: sharp, bright colors, and everything in focus?

Introducing SOAP, the LoRA that makes SDXL "photos" look like they were shot on a mobile phone (and not in portrait mode!) Sharper, brighter tones, and less bokeh. This LoRA will make the background of your images come to life.

No need to use any activation word, just apply this LoRA and watch the magic. I recommend using it at 25% for mild effect, and 50% for a strong effect.

Recommended settings on Auto1111: Euler, CFG 4-5, strength 0.25 - 0.5

A REQUEST: If this LoRA blows you away, like it has me, please remember to come back and post sample images and vote! Thanks for giving it a try.

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both bagpipe_arknights.pt and bagpipe_arknights.safetensors, then use bagpipe_arknights.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use bagpipe_arknights.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is bagpipe_arknights, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, solo, {bagpipe_arknights:1.10}, horns, long_hair, orange_hair, bangs, smile, very_long_hair, purple_eyes, dragon_horns, breasts, open_mouth, blush, large_breasts, blue_eyes, 1girl, :d, looking_at_viewer.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Bagpipe Arknights

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/bagpipe_arknights, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/bagpipe_arknights, which may be helpful to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

A SDXL 1.0 LoRa made by AI_Characters for improving the photographic capabilities of the base SDXL 1.0 model. It makes the photos look more realistic, less fake and AI generated, and overall just higher quality - with slight improvements to NSFW as well.

Usage recommendations

Weight: 1.0 (may need to be adjusted down when using in conjunction with other LoRa's) Model: SDXL 1.0 with 0.9 vae Generation parameters: 35 steps | DPM++ 2M Karras | CFG 7 Negative prompt: text, watermark, low-quality, signature, moirÃ© pattern, downsampling, aliasing, distorted, blurry, glossy, blur, jpeg artifacts, compression artifacts, poorly drawn, low-resolution, bad, distortion, twisted, excessive, exaggerated pose, exaggerated limbs, grainy, symmetrical, duplicate, error, pattern, beginner, pixelated, fake, hyper, glitch, overexposed, high-contrast, bad-contrast with only the "G" text encoder enabled (see my article here for how to do that)

Trigger words

  • "photo in phst artstyle"

  • "with beautiful lighting"

Changelog

v2.0

  • Complete revision - trained with a much lower learning rate but more epochs, leading to increased likeness, flexibility, and variety; fixed the eyes issue that may have been a preemptive victory celebration - eyes are definitely better now but still a bit worse than base SDXL; slightly improved NSFW

v1.0

  • Initial release

Additional Info

Credit is not mandatory but I would still appreciate credit when posting images using these LoRa's on social media! Feel free to @ my Twitter and/or Instagram accounts too (@ai_characters)! I would love to know when it is used!

I share all of my model's and training knowledge for free, but donations to my Ko-Fi would be greatly appreciated! Testing so much and training so many model's costs a lot of money (and time).

Feel free to also try out my RVC2 AI voice models which you can find here!

See here for an extensive article about my entire training workflow and configuration if you want to train your own SDXL 1.0 LoRa's and achieve results similar as me!

Stats (v2.0)

Dataset:

  • 311x photos

Epoch chosen for the final model:

items.name: Shared Umbrella | LoRA
items.description:
The recommended values are 0.7-0.9

Trigger words:

  • umbrella(more chances of generating a good image if you include the color of it)

  • shared umbrella

  • holding umbrella

Beware that the model is quite tricky and the results may include errors such as multiple umbrellas, lack of a hand that is holding it, etc, but it does get the job done within a few generations.

My advice would be to generate without using the highres at first, and then plug it into highres using the seed.

Enjoy!

If you like the model, you are free to share your creations, I really like seeing everyone's results! :)
